Mutabor core functionality

This group contains the functions that deal with the core idea of Mutabor: Parse Mutabor source files and use the generated memory structures to manage tunings, logics and retunings. Mehr ...

Zusammengehörigkeiten von Mutabor core functionality:

Ausführliche Beschreibung

This group contains the functions that deal with the core idea of Mutabor: Parse Mutabor source files and use the generated memory structures to manage tunings, logics and retunings.

454  internal_error,
455  _("Changing tone system width with incompatible parameters. Please report to the MUTABOR team."));
456  break;
457  }
458  asprintf(&name, _("%s:[<<@%c%d>>]"),
459  name,
460  aktion->u.aufruf_umst_breite_rel.rechenzeichen,
461  parameters->data[0]);
462  help = box->tonesystem->breite;
463 
464  switch (aktion->u.aufruf_umst_breite_rel.rechenzeichen) {
465 
466  case '+':
467  help += parameters->data[0];
468  break;
469 
470  case '-':
471  help -= parameters->data[0];
472  break;
473 
474  case '*':
475  help *= parameters->data[0];
476  break;
477 
478  case '/':
479  help /= parameters->data[0];
480  break;
481  }
482 
483  change_breite(box, help);
484  update_pattern(box);
485 #ifdef NOTES_CORRECT_SOFORT
486  NotesCorrect(box);
487 #endif
488  mutabor_update(box, mutabor_keys_changed || mutabor_box_changed);
489  }
490  break;
491 
492  case aufruf_umst_toene_veraendert: {
493  long * ton_zeiger;
494  struct ton_einstell * lauf;
495  TRACE;
496  asprintf(&name, _("%s:[.,.,.]"),
497  aktion->name?aktion->name:"");
498 
499  for (ton_zeiger = box->tonesystem->ton,
500  lauf = aktion->u.aufruf_umst_toene_veraendert.tonliste;
501  lauf;
502  lauf = lauf->next, ton_zeiger ++) {
503 
504  switch (lauf->ton_einstell_typ) {
505 
506  case einstell_stumm:
507  * ton_zeiger = 0;
508 
509  break;
510 
511  case einstell_gleich:
512  /* nichts tun */
513  break;
514 
515  case einstell_absolut:
516  * ton_zeiger = lauf->u.einstell_absolut.wert;
517 
518  break;
519 
520  case einstell_relativ:
521  * ton_zeiger += lauf->u.einstell_relativ.wert;
522 
523  break;
524 
525  }
526 
527  }
528 
529 #ifdef NOTES_CORRECT_SOFORT
530  NotesCorrect(box);
531 
532 #endif
533  mutabor_update(box, mutabor_keys_changed || mutabor_box_changed);
534  }
535  break;
536 
537  case aufruf_umst_umst_bund: {
538  TRACE;
539 
540  if (aktion->name) {
541  char * params, * oldparams;
542  if (parameters->size)
543  asprintf(&params, "%d", parameters->data[0]);
544  for (int i = 1; i < parameters->size; i++) {
545  oldparams = params;
546  asprintf(&params, _("%s,%d"),
547  oldparams,
548  parameters->data[i]);
549  free(oldparams);
550  }
551  asprintf(&name, "%s(%s)",aktion->name,params);
552  }
553 
554  /* nothing to be done here, this is only the head (containing the name) of the compound,
555  */
556  break;
557  }
558  case aufruf_umst_umst_case: {
559  struct case_element * lauf;
560  int i;
561  TRACE;
562  if (!parameters ||
563  parameters->size != 1 ||
564  !parameters->data) {
565  mutabor_error_message(box,
566  internal_error,
567  _("Switching cases with incompatible parameter list. Please report to the MUTABOR team."));
568  break;
569  }
570  i=parameters->data[0];
571  asprintf(&name, "%s { %d:", aktion->name?aktion->name:"", i);
572  mutabor_log_action(box, name);
573 
574  for (lauf = aktion->u.aufruf_umst_umst_case.umst_case;
575  lauf;
576  lauf = lauf->next) {
577  if ( (i == lauf->case_wert) || (lauf->is_default)) {
578  call_actions (box,
579  lauf->case_aktion,
580  parameters);
581  // return would break further execution
582  break;
583  }
584  }
585  name = strdup("}");
586  }
587  break;
588 
589  case aufruf_midi_out: {
590  char * parameters, * oldparameters;
591  struct midiliste * i = aktion->u.aufruf_midi_out.out_liste;
592  if (i) {
593  asprintf(&parameters,"%x",i->midi_code);
594  i = i->next;
595  } else parameters = NULL;
596  for (; i ; i = i->next) {
597  oldparameters = parameters;
598  asprintf(&parameters, _("%s %x"),
599  oldparameters,
600  i -> midi_code);
601  free(oldparameters);
602  }
603  if (parameters) {
604  asprintf(& name,"%s: MidiOut(%s)",aktion->name?aktion->name:"",parameters);
605  } else {
606  strdup(name);
607  }
608 
609  mutabor_midi_out(box, aktion->u.aufruf_midi_out.out_liste);
610  }
611  break;
612 
613  case aufruf_harmony_analysis:
614  name=strdup("HarmonyAnalysis");
615  HarmonyAnalysis(box, &(box->pattern));
616 
617  default:
618  mutabor_error_message(box,
619  internal_error,
620  _("Unexpected action type: %d"), aktion->aufruf_typ);
621  UNREACHABLE;
622  name = strdup("???");
623  }
624  mutabor_log_action(box, name);
625  free(name);
626  }
627 
628 
629 #if 0
630 #ifndef NOTES_CORRECT_SOFORT
631  mutabor::NotesCorrect(box);
632 #endif
633 #endif
634  }

double mutabor_convert_interval_to_pitch ( mutabor_interval  interval)
inline

Convert an interval to half tone based pitch according to MIDI pitch numbers.

The microtonal part is retained in the double return value.

Parameter
intervalInterval in the internal representation of Mutabor.
Rückgabe
a double value that represents the interval. a half tone is represented as 1.00, and an octave as 12.00.

Find a key in the given box.

Parameter
boxBox to be seached in.
keyKey number to be found.

Rückgabe
index of the key structure that has been found our 0 otherwise.
